						<div class="postbody">If you were doing this though, wouldn't you have to duplicate a bunch of tiles to be on both sprite tables? Basically, you have to reserve half of vram for sprites even if you really only need about 24KB. The main problem I see with this though is that you'd have to update vram twice for one object. Maybe your code could look to see where you object is vertically and only update the table that corresponds to what part of the screen it's on? You'd still have to write to both if it is in the dead center.</div>

